      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 bgcolor='#000066' class='spti2'>ITEM COMMENTS</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>AWESOME!</span><b>, By Svadilfare</b> <small>(1/31/2001)</small><br><br>This is IMO definately one of the best if not the best epic quest item I have seen.  You can summon this bad boy, summon the pet, give orb to pet.  Then just summon another, it might wipe out your mana, but really you are just storing it for later=).  

I think it is a great idea that the mage gets a spell as his epic.  
In fact, i wonder why Verant didnt make the other int casters have spells for their epic.  After all, weapons are for warriors; deeper knowledge in the arcane arts is what casters should strive for.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>500 ISN</span><b>, By Wiglet</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>At lvl 54, which is the minimum lvl for mage epic quest, you have 2,268 mana if your at 200 Int. You can cast the spell 4 times if you want, before your out of mana, besides, it's not no rent, it's no DROP, you can go ld all you want and still have it!<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>GEEZ...</span><b>, By Nel</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br><p>This epic is great, i only wish people would read. The epic is <em>not no rent</em>, so therefore it wont pop when you go ld or camp.</p>
<p>Second, by the time you can summon the next rod your pet will
still be alive, so you hand the rod off to the pet and summon
another rod, it's that easy, then once that pet dies, you just
right click and repeat.I dont even want to go into the fact that
it doesnt require any regents and you can summon it at any time,
specifically after dying. Also, this rod only costs 100mana more
then are highest pet summon. wow im surprised that any of the
people here couldnt like this item, maybe you arent even mages.
Either way, im close to getting it and I know i'm gonna love it.</p><br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>WHAT A JOKE</span><b>, By Kymber of solusek ro</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br><p>This Item that we have to summon may have great stats and look
cool. But it is a complete JOKE. What most seem to have
overlooked is in high level hunts you spend a bunch of time on CR
(corpse recovery) if you have 1 summoned you are stuck like
everyone else as it is a lore item. The Fact that it takes 500
mana to summon is a watse... We should have it about 100 mana to
summon the staff as it has a 5 minute recast time. All I have to
say is if you get one cast it make your pet and toss the
staff..... you'll need to summon one for your CR.</p><br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>ARE YOU ALL CRAZY!!!!</span><b>, By Novar spellweaver,lvl 29 mage.</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br><p>Ok, i'm only a lowley 29th level but i'll tell you what: if
any of you dont want your epic items, come on to Brell server and
help me get mine! I'd love to have a staff with those stats and a
monstor pet to do my bidding... all for ..ummm... well mana? Geee
what a pain ....NOT ... its only mana!!!!!! Think about it. Just
my oppinion.</p><br><hr size='1'></td>
